&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of a Medical Laboratory Assistant is varied and involves providing support to the scientific staff (Biomedical Scientists) and as such is a key role in sustaining a quality diagnostic service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work includes the receipt, sorting, preparation and processing of patient samples, maintaining stocks of consumable items, disposal of biological waste, operating and maintaining laboratory equipment as well as general housekeeping duties and clerical tasks including data input of patient demographics and test request information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We expect you to be a passionate, self-motivated individual who has an organised approach to work with good attention to detail and who can remain calm when busy. You will possess well developed communication and observational skills and enjoy working as part of a team so together we can provide excellent care and quality in a challenging environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience in an NHS clinical laboratory or in analytical techniques would be an advantage but is not essential as full training will be provided. What is important to have is a positive attitude; experience of working effectively in a busy team environment, performing work which may have been repetitive in nature but requires good concentration and attention to detail is also experience that we are looking for. A good level of secondary education is required with English, Maths and Science to GCSE (Grade A-C) or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is based at Queen&#39;s Medical Centre Campus. Vacancies are fixed term contracts or secondment for 6 months in the first instance with a view for extension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours: Sunday-Sunday 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
